label.value: Metastatic Childhood Ovarian Germ Cell Tumor by Toronto Guidelines v2

value.value: Distant metastatic disease excluding peritoneal metastases. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Arsenic Trioxide/Daunorubicin Regimen

value.value: A regimen consisting of arsenic trioxide and daunorubicin that may be used in the treatment of acute promyelocytic leukemia (APL).

label.value: Arsenic Trioxide/Daunorubicin/Tretinoin Regimen

value.value: A regimen consisting of arsenic trioxide, daunorubicin and tretinoin that may be used in the treatment of acute promyelocytic leukemia (APL).

label.value: Metastatic Malignant Ovarian Germ Cell Tumor

value.value: A malignant germ cell tumor that arises from the ovary and has spread to another anatomic site.

label.value: Childhood Ovarian Germ Cell Tumor by Toronto Guidelines v2 Stage, Tier 2

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of childhood ovarian germ cell tumor according to the tier 2 Toronto childhood cancer staging guidelines v2.

label.value: Stage I Childhood Ovarian Germ Cell Tumor by Toronto Guidelines v2

value.value: Tumor confined to ovaries (one or both). (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Stage II Childhood Ovarian Germ Cell Tumor by Toronto Guidelines v2

value.value: Tumor involves one or both ovaries with pelvic extension (below the pelvic brim). (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Stage III Childhood Ovarian Germ Cell Tumor by Toronto Guidelines v2

value.value: Tumor involves one or both ovaries with cytologically or histologically confirmed spread to the peritoneum outside the pelvis and/or metastasis to the retroperitoneal lymph nodes. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Stage IV Childhood Ovarian Germ Cell Tumor by Toronto Guidelines v2

value.value: Distant metastasis (excludes peritoneal metastases). (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Transcription Activator BRG1

value.value: Transcription activator BRG1 (1647 aa, ~185 kDa) is encoded by the human SMARCA4 gene. This protein plays a role in the mediation of both chromatin remodeling and transcription.

label.value: Childhood Astrocytoma by Toronto Guidelines v2 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of childhood astrocytoma according to the Toronto childhood cancer staging guidelines v2. This staging system is the same for both tiers (tier 1 and 2). (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Localized Childhood Astrocytoma by Toronto Guidelines v2

value.value: Localized disease. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Metastatic Childhood Astrocytoma by Toronto Guidelines v2

value.value: Distant metastases present. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Childhood Central Nervous System Embryonal Tumor by Toronto Guidelines v2 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of childhood central nervous system embryonal tumor according to the Toronto childhood cancer staging guidelines v2.

label.value: Childhood Central Nervous System Embryonal Tumor by Toronto Guidelines v2 Stage, Tier 1

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of childhood central nervous system embryonal tumor according to the tier 1 Toronto childhood cancer staging guidelines v2.

label.value: Codonopsis pilosula Supplement

value.value: A traditional Chinese medicine composed of the roots of Codonopsis pilosula, with potential immunostimulatory, anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities. Codonopsis pilosula contains the oligosaccharide inulin, various polysaccharides, sterols, alkaloids and triterpenoids. Upon administration, Codonopsis pilosula supplement may exert immunostimulatory, anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects, and enhance immunity and improve hematopoietic functions.

label.value: Localized Childhood Central Nervous System Embryonal Tumor by Toronto Guidelines v2

value.value: Localized disease. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Lymph Node Dissection Type

value.value: The type of lymphadenectomy performed.

label.value: Metastatic Childhood Central Nervous System Embryonal Tumor by Toronto Guidelines v2

value.value: Disease beyond local site (e.g., other lesions in brain or spine or tumor cells in CSF or distant metastases). (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Probable Global Transcription Activator SNF2L2

value.value: Probable global transcription activator SNF2L2 (1590 aa, ~181 kDa) is encoded by the human SMARCA2 gene. This protein is involved in the modulation of hormone receptor transcription factor activity.

label.value: Childhood Central Nervous System Embryonal Tumor by Toronto Guidelines v2 Stage, Tier 2

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of childhood central nervous system embryonal tumor according to the tier 2 Toronto childhood cancer staging guidelines v2.

label.value: Stage M0 Childhood Central Nervous System Embryonal Tumor by Toronto Guidelines v2

value.value: No visible disease on imaging (MRI brain and spine) beyond primary site of disease and no tumor cells in the CSF. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Stage M1 Childhood Central Nervous System Embryonal Tumor by Toronto Guidelines v2

value.value: Tumor cells in the CSF. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Stage M0

value.value: A stage term that refers to central nervous system embryonal tumor or ependymoma in which no visible tumor is detected beyond the primary site of disease on MRI imaging (brain and spine) and no tumor cells are found in the CSF.

label.value: Stage M1

value.value: A stage term that refers to central nervous system embryonal tumor or ependymoma in which tumor cells are present in the CSF.

label.value: Stage M3

value.value: A stage term that refers to central nervous system embryonal tumor or ependymoma in which visible metastasis is present in the spine or cervicomedullary junction.

label.value: Stage M4

value.value: A stage term that refers to central nervous system embryonal tumor or ependymoma in which the tumor has spread outside of the central nervous system.

label.value: Suspension for Gel Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a suspension intended to be mixed with the specified liquid or gel to obtain a gel (for cutaneous use).

label.value: Suspension and Gel for Gel Dosage Form

value.value: Suspension and gel intended for the preparation of a gel (for cutaneous use) by mixing the suspension in the gel. The suspension contains active ingredient(s); the gel does not contain active ingredient(s).

label.value: Administration Method of Administration

value.value: To administer a medication.

label.value: SWP82

value.value: SWP82, around 82 KD, is one of the subunits of SWI/SNF complex from S. cerevisiae.

label.value: Gas Cylinder Bundle

value.value: Container consisting of an assembly of cylinders suited for compressed, liquefied or dissolved gas, which are fastened together in a frame and interconnected by a manifold, and are transported and used as a single unit. It is fitted with a device to regulate the spontaneous outflow of gas at atmospheric pressure and room temperature.

label.value: Stage M2 Childhood Central Nervous System Embryonal Tumor by Toronto Guidelines v2

value.value: Visible metastasis in brain. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Stage M3 Childhood Central Nervous System Embryonal Tumor by Toronto Guidelines v2

value.value: Visible metastasis in spine or visible metastasis in cervicomedullary junction. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

value.value: Metastasis outside of the central nervous system. (Childhood cancer staging for population registries according to the Toronto Childhood Cancer Stage Guidelines - Version 2. Cancer Council Queensland and Cancer Australia: Brisbane, Australia; 2021.)

label.value: Stage M0 Childhood Medulloblastoma by Toronto Guidelines v2

value.value: No visible disease on imaging (MRI brain and spine) beyond primary site of disease and no tumor cells in the CSF. label.value: SWP61

value.value: A component of the SWI/SNF global transcription activator complex and the RSC chromatin remodeling complex, SWP61 assists gene-specific activators through nucleosome/chromatin remodeling.  The SWI/SNF complex is required for induced expression of many genes and alters chromatin structure to facilitate binding of gene-specific dedicated transcription factors.  Actin-related SWP61 is a non-specific DNA-binding RNA polymerase II transcription factor.  (from SGD S0006238 and NCI)
